B14 - Teach friends about cybersecurity topic of your choice

Objective
the goal of this activity was to teach friends about basci cybersecurity concepts and improve their awareness of common digital  threats

Method
i explained key cybersecurity concepts in casual discussion with friends, focusing on real-world examples they encounter in daily life such as social media, messaging apps, and online accounts. i used simple explanations and encourages questions to ensure understanding.

Content delivered
1. strong password policies - i explained why weak passwords are easy to guess and recommended using long, unique passwords or passphrases
2. multi-factor authentication - i explained how MFA adds an extra layer of security beyond passwords, making it significantly harder for attackers to access accounts even if passwords are compromised
3. phishing awareness - i described how phishing messages and emails attempt to trick users into clicking malicious links or revealing personal information
4. public wifi risks - i explained how unsecured public wifi networks cane xpose users to data interception and why secure netowrks or VPNs improve security

Outcome
my friends gained a better understanding of common cybersecurity risks and became more aware of safe online practices such as verifying links, using stronger passwords, and enabling MFA.

